<DOCNO> AP880623-0002 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
a black man walking home from his job at a 
fastfood restaurant was attacked early wednesday by six white men 
who shouted racial slurs as they pummelled him with sticks and a 
baseball bat police said 
the victim raymond buckner took refuge in a pizza parlor 
where the owners defended him against the gang and were themselves 
later harassed and assaulted according to police 
three whites were arrested and police were seeking three others 
buckner 24 was treated for bruises at a hospital and released 
he said the assault which occurred on staten island reminded 
him of the attack by a dozen white youths on three blacks in the 
howard beach section of queens in december 1986 
in that highly publicized case one of the black men died when 
he was hit by a car while trying to escape three white teens were 
convicted of manslaughter last december 
its the same incident racial said buckner who was 
treated for contusions at st vincents hospital i was minding 
my own business i just get jumped for no reason 
a short time after the attack officers arrested frank dessoye 
19 steven p russell 18 and michael kish 20 all of staten 
island 
they were charged with seconddegree assault aggravated 
harassment criminal possession of a deadly instrument and 
possession of a controlled substance marijuana dessoye was also 
charged with driving while intoxicated 
howard beach was the first thing i thought of said jeff 
lamartina one of the owners of the cafe disicilia pizzeria who 
aided buckner it wasnt right this guy was doing nothing 
wrong 
buckner a cook at a burger king restaurant said he was walking 
home through a mostly white section of staten island at about 1220 
am when a car slowed down and the occupants began harassing him 
they were calling me racial names nigger blackie buckner 
said the men left their car and began beating him on the arm with 
sticks and a baseball bat chasing him down the street 
when buckner fled into the pizzeria he was nervous his arm 
was messed up lamartina said he said he just got jumped by a 
carload of white guys 
lamartina gave buckner some ice and offered to have a worker 
drive him home the group of white men appeared in front of the 
store but they left after lamartina and an employee went outside 
to disperse them 
at about 120 am after buckner had been taken home the group 
reappeared in front of the pizza parlor and taunted lamartina and 
the stores other owner sal taormina calling them nigger 
lovers lamartina said both owners are white 
one of them had a bat and went to swing it at me but sal 
caught it lamartina recounted we smacked them around a little 
bit and they ran away 
neighbors who had witnessed the altercation called police as 
did buckner when he got home 
a short time later officers pulled over a red car and arrested 
frank dessoye 19 steven p russell 18 and michael kish 20 all 
of staten island they were identified by buckner lamartina and 
taormina as the assailants 
the three men were charged with seconddegree assault 
aggravated harassment criminal possession of a deadly instrument 
and criminal possession of a controlled substance marijuana 
dessoye was also charged with driving while intoxicated 
all three pleaded innocent to the charges before criminal court 
judge michael j brennan bail was set for dessoye at 5275 and 
2500 for both russell and kish 
</TEXT>
