<TEXT>
a new film talent has emerged from the satirical 
movie a handful of dust her name is kristin scott thomas 
the movie features alec guinness and anjelica huston in small 
but telling cameos but it is dominated by scott thomas as the 
elegant english rose lady brenda last who drifts into a 
destructive affair with the young roue john beaver rupert graves 
based on evelyn waughs savage 1934 novel the 6 million film 
costars james wilby graves costar last year in maurice as 
lady brendas hapless husband tony it opens in new york on june 
24 
im very pleased im afraid about the reaction that im 
getting its so nice to have ones work appreciated scott 
thomas said in an interview about her repeated raves from the 
british press 
while reviews were mixed for the movie as a whole critics 
hailed its female lead with the kind of accolades that banish 
anonymity forever 
alexander walker in the standard called the actress the films 
great find adding it will be criminal if british cinema 
doesnt make a great star of her 
hugh montgomerymassingberd in the daily telegraph and derek 
malcolm in the guardian both called her a revelation iain 
johnstone in the sunday times found the parisbased actress a 
singular sensation in a movie that has returned her in triumph to 
the country she left eight years ago 
i never really thought id be able to work in england so a 
handful of dust was an enormous pleasure and a great privilege 
said the 28yearold actress who dropped out of londons central 
school of speech and drama after a year to move to paris 
i was doing a teacher training course and hated it wanted to 
change and couldnt said scott thomas occasionally interrupting 
the interview to tend to the cries of her monthold daughter 
hannah 
i was told id never be an actress anyway and would never be 
able to play for real she said i thought it would be better 
to be totally miserable somewhere else and learn french at the same 
time 
in paris her life took a happier turn beginning with her 
marriage to a french obstetrician after drama training in french 
she began getting parts in theater and in movies and landed a role 
opposite the rock superstar prince in his second movie a bomb 
called under the cherry moon 
the film was not a financial success and was lampooned by 
critics however it enjoyed an international release charles 
sturridge the director of handful of dust and of the hit waugh 
tv adaptation brideshead revisited saw it and cast scott 
thomas as lady brenda 
she had studied the book at school and said she seized the 
chance to become part of the film 
i was sure it was going to be great she recalled before 
going back to the novel to immerse herself in lady brendas 
emotionally fatal attraction to the callow and cunning beaver 
she likes taking someone who is absolutely dreadful and 
turning him into this fascinating young man whom no one can 
understand what she sees in him scott thomas said explaining 
the fascination on which the films denouement depends it makes 
her different too 
in the end beaver is much worse than lady brenda ever thought 
he was really by then shes in too deep she said 
the daughter of an affluent naval officer who died when she was 
five scott thomas said she was bemused by the critique of the 
english class system that pervades the book and the film 
its quite sort of endearing really but it is ridiculous 
said scott thomas a graduate of the posh cheltenham ladies 
college its like some dear old piece of furniture that you like 
but you think is quite the most hideous thing in the world 
she hopes not to be typecast as aristocratic english swells and 
would like to do a french film next 
i live there and i want to work there you have to work hard 
and i really mean to work hard she said ive got to make sure 
that the revelation doesnt turn out to be a disaster 
</TEXT>
