<TEXT>
congressional negotiators working on a 
pentagon budget bill have scaled back plans for a major military 
role in the antidrug effort and have cut president reagans 
request for star wars spending sources said 
the housesenate conference committee has approved all but a few 
details of a pentagon budget for the fiscal year starting oct 1 
and expect to complete their work later this week the sources who 
spoke on condition of anonymity told the associated press 
an agreement will send the huge bill back to the senate and 
house floors for approval and it will then go to reagan for his 
signature 
the bill authorizes 2995 billion in defense spending for the 
upcoming fiscal year down slightly from the 300 billion the 
pentagon is allowed to spend in the current year 
the sources said wednesday that the conference committee agreed 
to increase spending for an antidrug program in which coast guard 
officers ride aboard navy warships patrolling in offshore waters 
the coast guard officers have civilian arrest powers that they 
can use if the navy vessels encounter suspected drugtrafficking 
boats 
the coast guard has about 300 people assigned to the program 
riding aboard navy ships in teams of five to seven people per 
vessel another 100 coast guard personnel will be added to the 
program in the next three months the sources said 
the house had voted overwhelmingly to order reagan to have the 
pentagon essentially seal us borders against illegal drug 
shipments 
later the senate easily voted to give navy officers civilian 
arrest powers if warships stopped suspected drug trafficking 
vessels in international waters 
but the pentagon strongly opposed both those provisions defense 
secretary frank c carlucci said the military shouldnt get 
involved in civilian law enforcement and warned that even if it 
did illegal drugs still would flow into the united states 
the final compromise while dropping the more farreaching 
antidrug provisions passed by each chamber requires the pentagon 
to increase the help it provides to civilian antidrug agencies in 
spotting and tracking planes and ships that might be carrying 
contraband 
the air force and navy already provide intelligence help from 
radar planes and ships and carlucci said he has no opposition to 
increasing that aid 
the conference committee meanwhile agreed to authorize 41 
billion for star wars formally known as the strategic defense 
initiative the sources said that is up from the current 39 
billion budget but far below the 48 billion reagan had sought 
in addition the conferees dropped an amendment approved by the 
house that would have required a halt in all but the smallest us 
nuclear weapons tests the senate had rejected the proposed ban 
the legislators also agreed to authorize 250 million each for 
the midgetman and mx programs a pair of controversial efforts to 
develop new landbased atomictipped weapons another 250 million 
was approved for spending after a new president is elected nov 8 
the sources said 
