utley who died tuesday worked for the daily telegraph voice 
of british conservatism for 21 years rising to the posts of 
assistant editor and chief editorial writer 
his essays and analyses won him respect as an oracle of 
conservative ideology and a scholar of the northern ireland 
question 
born thomas edwin utley he took the byline te utley but was 
known throughout the newspaper world as peter blinded by disease 
at age 9 he adopted the black eyepatch that became his hallmark 
taught himself braille and graduated from oxford university with 
honors 
utley reveled in poking fun at his handicap often insisting 
that as far as he could remember cars still had running boards he 
spurned the white stick preferring to be led about by promising 
young journalists whose careers he wanted to promote 
