rainfall by as much as 10 percent but he noted for cloud 
seeding to work it needs some clouds so if there are no clouds 
youre out of luck that same thought was echoed by the other 
meteorologists 
the atmosphere just does not have any clouds in it weve been 
totally cloud free braham said 
weve been in the field since june 1 but weve flown very 
litte added boe whose agency operates an airborne cloudseeding 
program covering 66 million acres of western north dakota 
north dakota spends about 15 million per twoyear budget cycle 
on weather modification half from the state and half from a tax 
voted by residents of the counties affected 
henderson said that the cost of running a commercial fourmonth 
summertime cloudseeding program covering 3000 to 5000 acres in 
the midwest would typically run from 100000 to 125000 
making it rain has obsessed mankind for thousands of years and 
many hoped for a breakthrough a few decades ago when the first 
successes were achieved 
in 1946 vincent j schaefer accomplished the goal although he 
actually made it snow rather than rain 
through the centuries all sorts of less scientific methods had 
been attempted including animal sacrifice setting out pots of 
water calling on various gods clashing armor ringing church 
bells and even firing artillery into the sky 
schaefer in a famous nov 13 1946 experiment near 
schenectady ny sprinkled three pounds of ground dry ice into a 
cloud and within minutes snowflakes formed and a hole appeared in 
the cloud 
a lot of experimentation was done in the 1970s sponsored by 
state and federal governments but there has been relatively little 
scientific work on changing the weather in the 1980s 
that is partly because of reductions in money available for the 
work and partly because the scientists succeeded in defining the 
situations where rainfall increases looked feasible and those where 
it didnt look so feasible and the window of opportunity kept 
getting smaller and smaller braham said 
boe stressed that any cloudseeding program has to be a 
continuing one 
if youre going to start a weather modification program to 
deal with drought and when its over you bag the program youre 
taking the wrong tack he said longterm cloud seeding adds to 
the deep ground moisture and can help resist the damage of 
droughts 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> AP880623-0080 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
newly elected prime minsiter do muoi 
said today that hanoi is trying to end its international isolation 
by seeking to end its 9yearold military occupation of cambodia 
the official voice of vietnam radio quoted do muoi as saying 
vietnam may withdraw all of its troops from cambodia before 1990 
according to the broadcast do muoi said that to widen 
cooperation first of all it is necessary to maintain peace and 
security vietnam is striving to solve the cambodian issue 
do muoi 71 was elected on wednesday 
many noncommunist western and asian countries have denied 
economic aid to vietnam and otherwise isolated the communist nation 
to protest its late 1978 invasion and continuing occupation of 
cambodia 
vietnam has said it will remove all its estimated 120000 troops 
by 1990 and plans a pullout of about 50000 troops this year 
todays announcement was the first time a vietnamese leader said 
the withdrawal could be completed before that date 
hanoibased diplomats say that under a new pragmatic leadership 
that has given top priority to economic development vietnam has 
made a series of diplomatic initiatives on cambodia which not long 
ago was a nonnegotiable issue 
vietnam recently decided to send foreign minister nguyen co 
thach to attend unprecedented peace talks involving cambodian 
guerrilla factions next month in indonesia 
in a speech wednesday do muoi pledged to continue vietnams 
westernstyle economic reforms to revive an economy communist 
authorities said they weakened through indecisiveness and poor 
planning 
an official radio hanoi report seen in bangkok today quoted do 
muoi as telling the national assembly he will thoroughly grasp 
the renovative spirit of resolutions adopted at a december 1986 
party congress 
the resolutions liberalized vietnams economy by allowing a 
measure of free enterprise and opening up the country to foreign 
investment 
in a report to the assembly wednesday vo van kiet the acting 
premier said people were deeply worried about rampant 
inflation chaos in the distribution of goods and acute food 
shortages in the northern provinces 
vietnamese sources had said do muoi was the most likely choice 
as premier because he is a disciplinarian who can crack down on the 
corruption and inefficiency among cadres involved in implementing 
economic reforms 
some diplomats say the choice of do muoi could slow down the 
reform momentum sending a wrong signal to the average vietnamese 
who preferred kiet 66 a pioneer of economic reform 
kiet was first vice premier before becoming acting premier after 
pham hungs death the radio report did not say whether he would 
return to the old post 
do muoi is the thirdranking member of the politburo the top 
policymaking body he gave up the vice premiership last year after 
becoming the no 2 man in the party secretariat where he is said 
to have directed a purge of inept and corrupt elements in the 
18millionmember party 
he joined the communist party in 1939 and held key party and 
government posts during the struggle against the french 
colonialists the americans and south vietnam 
