linda and tom wolfe discovered 
marylands motto when their son wrote a history report and began 
another campaign to persuade the general assembly to change a motto 
they consider sexist 
the motto in italian fatti maschii parole femine means 
manly deeds and womanly words according to the states 
accepted translation 
there it was right on the seal it is pretty disgusting 
mrs wolfe said recently she and her husband have formed momma or 
modernization of marylands motto association 
since midmay about 400 people have signed the wolfes petition 
which hangs on the cash register at their college park store the 
smile herb shop they hope to have 3000 signatures on the petition 
when they submit it to state officials 
the wolfes are not the first to try to change the motto in 
1978 a joint resolution requested a legislative committee to 
devise a more appropriate state motto 
the motto is incompatible with the equal rights and privileges 
accorded to women by the constitution of the united states read 
the bill which died in the senate 
during the past three centuries scholars have debated the 
mottos proper translation deeds are of more avail than words 
and act boldly but speak softly are among the less offensive 
