<TEXT>
beryl sprinkel chairman of president reagans 
council of economic advisers took a lot of heat in the months 
after the stock market crash for seeing the world through 
rosecolored glasses and predicting strong steady economic growth 
this year 
many private economists had issued deeply pessimistic 
