speaking of westmoreland when the king of thailand learned the 
general was planning a visit in may 1968 he invited the general 
over to talk since thai troops were serving with the allied forces 
in vietnam but mrs westmoreland who was accompanying her 
husband was excluded as the charge daffaires of the us embassy 
in bangkok explained in this cable to westmoreland 
we have learned from the kings chief aidedecamp that his 
majesty is looking forward to a rather lengthy serious discussion 
of the war with you and his aide expressed the view that this 
might be tiresome for the ladies since i take this to be a clear 
indication of the kings preference for a serious stag talk i am 
inclined to let it rest that way accordingly we have planned 
the itinerary with this in view 
</TEXT>
