<TEXT>
the communist party conference opening tuesday 
will be the 19th such gathering in soviet history and the first 
since 1941 
here are highlights from some past party conferences which 
under present rules can be called at any time to consider urgent 
questions of party policy 
first communist party conference held by russian 
revolutionaries at an exile base in tammerfors finland in 1905 
the year of a bloody unsuccessful uprising that set the stage for 
the collapse of the monarchy 12 years later and the bolshevik 
revolution that brought the communists to power 
seven party conferences were held in paris prague and other 
cities outside russia as revolutionaries plotted the overthrow of 
czar nicholas ii 
1912 the prague conference votes to create an allrussian 
workers newspaper which is today the official party organ pravda 
1924 a party conference held days before the death of soviet 
founder vladimir lenin condemned leon trotsky and his followers 
signaling the rise of josef stalin who was to lead the soviet 
state for most of the next three decades 
1929 the 16th party conference approves the first fiveyear 
plan the keystone of what has become a cumbersome centrally 
managed economy 
the 16th conference also ordered a purge of party ranks that 
presaged stalins mass political repression of the late 1930s 
1941 the 18th party conference orders party organizations to 
oversee the management of industry and transport as the nation 
rushes to prepare for war with germany 
the partys entanglement in practically all governmental and 
economic affairs which grew from the resolutions of the 16th and 
18th conferences is a key target of soviet leader mikhail s 
gorbachevs decentralization drive 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> AP880623-0246 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
no specific agenda has been announced for the 19th 
communist party conference but delegates may consider a wide range 
issues put before them by the policymaking central committee or by 
speakers recognized by the conference leadership 
whether specific recommendations emerge from the debate could 
provide an indication of whether soviet party leader mikhail s 
gorbachev or more conservative forces among the delegates control 
the conference 
the conference starts tuesday and is now expected to last at 
least four days among the matters likely to be raised 
the partys role gorbachev has said he wants to get party 
workers out of the hair of state and industry managers the party 
he said should focus on political and ideological work rather 
than try to rule every aspect of soviet life 
stalinism the conference will play a role in the effort to 
come to terms with the legacy of josef stalin who ran the soviet 
union with an iron hand for nearly 30 years part of that legacy 
has been a cult of personality now condemned he also developed 
the command economcy with all decisions made in the kremlin 
and passed down to individual factories and farms 
party control gorbachevs reformminded followers may press 
for new rules to limit party officials to two fiveyear terms and 
could set a mandatory retirement age perhaps 75 the move would 
shake up the entrenched party bureaucracy that is seen as an 
obstacle to reform and enable gorbachev to bring in new blood to 
help press his modernization program known as perestroika or 
restructuring 
expansion of multicandidate elections conducted by secret 
ballot to all party offices up to the 300plus members of the 
central committee is another proposal 
official powers an overhaul of the legal system to protect 
individual rights and insulate the system from political pressure 
is among the topics up for discussion 
there also are proposals for some form of separation of powers 
making the supreme soviet now largely a rubberstamp parliament 
that follows the will of the party an independent representative 
legislature 
economy under increasing pressure to show some tangible 
results of perestroika gorbachev could ask the conference to 
recommend changes in economic policy particularly in agriculture 
where soviet officials say permitting families to lease farms from 
their collectives could produce a dramatic increase in the nations 
food supply a constant subject of consumer complaints 
